HEADWORD: Photophore
<hw>Pho"to*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A form of endoscope using an electric
light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A light-emitting organ; specif.,
one of the luminous spots on certain marine (mostly deep-sea)
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photoprint</ent>⟦br⟧
